notesStmt.note: Title from title of first text (p. [1]) and title of second text (p. [249]); alternate title from introduction to second text (p. [1]).

msContents.summary: Two commentaries with the source-text in red and the commentary in brown. The first is on law and the Maliki madhhab and the second is on the orthography and readings of the Qurʼān.

supportDesc.extent: 125 leaves : 260 x 184 (205 x 130)mm, bound to 265 x 200 mm
supportDesc.foliation: With a few numbering errors, each work is paginated individually in pencil, upper left recto (only rectos are numbered) ([1]-284, [1]-248) ; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribi script in brown ink.

binding.p: Copy is disbound. Covers are brown leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II). Covers are blind stamped with central mandorla and have a blind tooled frame. Flap has coordinating stamp and tooling.

origin.p: Copy is dated 23 Ramadan 1106 A.H. (7 May 1695); probably copied in North Africa.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Marcus Jastrow and Morris Jastrow, Jr.
